Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper uses logical and algebraic methods to study games.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is likely because the paper deals with combinatorial games and their properties.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is likely because the paper extends Conway's theory of games and discusses game determinacy and strategies.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible because the paper discusses equivalences and congruences on games and hypergames, which can be related to complexity classes.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible because the paper discusses strategies and non-losing strategies in games, which can be relevant to AI agents playing games.
